begin_memory_text: My partner was a professor at a college in Texas, he teaches math. And he has been a teacher for about 12 years.
middle_memory_text: We talked about my career path, and me and my goals for becoming a lawyer.
end_memory_text: We talked about the LSAT and the questions in this test that I would need to face.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week, I see it going smoothly or rough. I have a lot of studying to do, and I have to catch up with a friend also I hope I can handle it. Part of my studying will include school and the other part will include studying for the LSAT,
critical_positive: What worked well about the conversation is I am a student and my partner was a professor. So it was cool to have another persons perspective about online schooling, and how the transition has been. It also worked well that we were both asking each other questions about the other persons life.
critical_negative: In the beginning of the conversation me and partner has the video chat lag numerous amount of times, it was a bit annoying. We then had to ask what the other person said again, and repeat our selfs. After the beginning of like the first five minutes, the video chat then went smoothly.

begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and each said what state we lived in. Then she told me that she was a student and just finished her midterms. I said that I was a professor.
middle_memory_text: I remember that we talked about our hobbies for a little bit. I mentioned that I had three kids and they kept me pretty busy. I told her that I liked to garden, read, and play video games. She asked me if I played the game "Among Us." I told her that I hadn't but that my kids were obsessed with it.
end_memory_text: Right toward the end we pivoted back to her interest in law school and taking the LSAT. She told me that she wanted to work as a lawyer who protected children from sex trafficking. She also told me about the logic portion of the LSAT and the essay that she'd need to write. I told her a little bit about what it was like to teach online.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of the week will be good. I need to get over an initial bunch of work before Monday. After I do, most of the week will be easy, since I won't have very much left to do. I need to gather my energy and do a lot of good work today.
critical_positive: My conversation partner did a very nice job thinking of questions to ask me. I was feeling kind of laid back, and letting her move the conversation forward at first. It worked well that she's a college student and I'm a professor, so we had a lot of things to discuss from two different perspectives.
critical_negative: I suppose there were a few moments where we both paused and were unsure what to say. These kinds of moments don't bother me in a conversation very much, but I think they're more awkward for some people. The problem was that we were searching for a topic to discuss that we were both interested in enough to go deeper. I think we eventually found some topics.
